** Assignment title**
**Prompt** Create a detailed album cover for an acoustic folk band. The central subject is a long-haired blond woman sitting on a wooden bench, her arms resting on her knees and her face looking straight ahead. Let the background be a green forest with tall pine trees. Have golden-hour sunlight stream through the pine trees, casting beams of light that fall directly over the musician. The edges of the forest must remain a dark, deep shadow that adds high volume. Add an acoustic guitar that is leaning against the bench and create a dark shadow underneath that adds contrast. Create the illusion of space by adding a light fog between the tall pine trees. Also add long shadows to the ground. Suggest time and motion by adding a slight breeze to the grass and the musician’s hair and clothes. The color palette that adds unity should revolve around earthy tones, warm browns and golds, all while introducing variety by adding a stream of blue orchids painted on the guitar.  The album cover has a symmetrical balance with the musician in the middle. The tall pine trees are evenly spaced out, creating an equal visual weight. The musician will remain the dominant focal point with a peaceful landscape.
